        {
          "username": "David",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "102329438400931129505",
          "user_review_count": 312,
          "user_photo_count": 283,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJvhX-xAWef0oijEVt7_q6P8HlSI9v08pI_I_5JRF128t7-D84=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I have to remark that this clinic made a lasting positive impression on me that supersedes a transient concern I had, still being a student. If I had to estimate, Sally must have spent at least fifteen minutes - if not longer - speaking with me, before starting on a very detailed cleaning. A filling placed by a previous dentist was smoothed, rather than re-filled. Something about her unique attention and genuine care resonated with me deeply. I'm updating this review up one more, to the full five stars it deserves: I remember a time I wanted to provide someone in my own sphere such an experience at a time they needed it, but I was strongly discouraged to do so by a supervisor. I can only imagine if that supervisor had to be a dentist or hygienist, they wouldn't have very good reviews! Patients always know who is best, and this is a remarkable clinic.\n\nThe quality and detail in her work are beyond comparison. My teeth were cleaned manually and much more effectively than how ultrasonic scaling is typically performed (and rushed) by most offices. I trust the doctor's assessment, and a worthwhile doctor is surrounded by great staff.",
